The paper deals with multi-label classification, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The proposed method also involves the use of embeddings, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), hence the sub-categories cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.CL are likely. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of unlabeled data, which is a common theme in semi-supervised learning, and the handling of missing labels, which is a common challenge in information retrieval (IR), hence cs.IR is also a likely sub-category.
